      1          /**
      2           *  @file       
      3           *
      4           *  @brief      The DtoA GDM for STM32G0x is a module that implements the
      5           *              DtoA Standard API (Application programming interface for the DtoA Channels) for the STM32G0x family of microcontrollers
      6           *
      7           *
      8           *  @details    The two 12-bit buffered DAC channels can be used to convert digital signals into analog
      9           *              voltage signal outputs.
     10           *
     11           *              DtoA channels are available in the below port-pins of STM32G0x -
     12           *               <pre>
     13           *               --------------------------------------
     14           *              | DTOA Channel   |  Port    |   Pin    |
     15           *              |----------------|----------|----------|
     16           *              |    DTOA_CH1    |   PORTA  |    4     |
     17           *              |----------------|----------|----------|
     18           *              |    DTOA_CH2    |   PORTA  |    5     |
     19           *               -------------------------------------- </pre>
     20           *
     21           *       The analog output voltage on each DAC channel pin is determined by the following equation:
     22           *
     23           *       DAC_OUTx = VREF+ * DOR / 4095
     24           *
     25           *       with  DOR is the Data Output Register
     26           *       VEF+ is the input voltage reference (refer to the device data sheet)
     27           *
     28           *       e.g. To set DAC_OUT1 to 0.7V, use
     29           *       Dtoa__SetValue(DTOA_CH1, 868);
     30           *       Assuming that VREF+ = 3.3, DAC_OUT1 = (3.3 * 868) / 4095 = 0.7V
     31           *
     32           *
     33           *       Supports only 12-bit and 8-bit resolution
     34           *       Continuous conversion feature is not implemented
     35           *
     36           *
     37           *
     38           *  @section    Applicable_Documents
     39           *                  List here all the applicable documents if needed. <tr>
     40           *
     41           *  $Header: $
     42           *
     43           *  @copyright  Copyright 2015-$Date$. Whirlpool Corporation. All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL
     44           */
